@18005 = ~Shady Document~
@18006 = ~A handwritten transcript, detailing a meeting between one Lady Katarina and Lord Dominick. An uncredited spy has crafted this extensive document, meticulously capturing even Lord Dominick's most banal ramblings. A few passages catch your eye:

Lady Katarina: I salute your taste, my Lord Dominick, exactly the delightful earthy tones you described—my, is that the bottle gone? One might suspect a less honorable and handsome man of plying me with drink. I jest, of course, my lord. Come, let us open another bottle to toast the hero of Baldur’s Gate! Tell me of how you met, again.
Dominick: I apologize, my lady. When I said I knew the hero, I meant more from... um, afar. I was in Baldur's Gate, when <PRO_HESHE> saved the city. My father ‘n I were visiting at the time.
Lady Katarina: Oh, what a sly rascal, to have deceived me so... You wouldn't lie to me now that we are such good friends, would you, my dear?
Dominick: Never, Miss Katarina. I can tell you what I know… <PRO_HESHE> was heralded a hero for thwarting the evil of Sarevok, but there were rumors that they both shared blood!
Lady Katarina: Do continue! I cannot deny an appetite for such gossip.
Dominick: Oh indeed… when they left the city—the lot of them—it was all but confirmed: both Sarevok and his slayer were… children of Bhaal…

The remainder of the transcript becomes increasingly incoherent, as Lord Dominick's inebriation overcomes intelligibility and then, eventually, consciousness.~

